@software{braffWPTA,
	title = {{WohlTemperiertesPhrasierApparat} ({WTPA}): A Max/{MSP} Implementation of Phrased Microtime},
	rights = {Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International},
	url = {https://zenodo.org/doi/10.5281/zenodo.19385028},
	doi = {10.5281/ZENODO.19385028},
	shorttitle = {{WohlTemperiertesPhrasierApparat} ({WTPA})},
	abstract = {{WohlTemperiertesPhrasierApparat} ({WTPA})

Malcolm Braff — Jazz Campus Basel, {FHNW} University of Applied Sciences and Arts First published: July 24, 2011 

Description

The {WTPA} ({WohlTemperiertesPhrasierApparat} — "Well-Tempered Phrasing Apparatus") is a Max/{MSP} patch implementing the concept of phrased microtime (groove) in real time. It is the first computational implementation of what later became the General Theory of Rhythm. 

